e hate speech and pornography and the capacity of democracies to address important practical problems in this highly anticipated volume cohen draws on his work in these diverse topics to develop an argument about what he calls following john rawls democracy's public reason he rejects the conventional idea that democratic politics is simply a contest for power and that philosophical argument is disconnected from life political philosophy he insists is part of politics and its job is to contribute to the public reasoning about what we ought to do at the heart of cohen's normative vision for our political life is an ideal of democracy in which citizens and their representatives deliberate about the requirements of justice and the common good it is an idealistic picture but also firmly grounded in the debates and struggles in which cohen has been engaged over nearly three decades philosophy politics democracy explores these debates and considers their implications for the practice of democratic politics topics democracy united states search cddrl search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages publication news new books released by cddrl faculty september 24 2009 cddrl fsi stanford news publications of interest reexamining democracy essays in honor of seymour martin lipset gary marks larry diamond sage 1992 buy+ cover policy coherence and incoherence the domestic politics of american democracy promotion matthew spence cddrl working papers 2005 pdf+ policy coherence and incorherance the domestic politics of american democracy promotion matthew spence d phil international relations oxford 2004 pdf+ the troubled birth of russian democracy politics parties programs and profiles michael a mcfaul sergei markov hoover institution press 1993 html+ cover support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4610 fax